description: 00:01 - This is a section from a guard instructional that I never quite finished. What I am going to talk about in the video is a bit outdated and I play DLR a bit differently now, but I think you will still find some insights from it.
04:42 - From the back on the underhook side, Craig takes a cross grip and traps the arm. He takes an elbow tie on the other arm to prevent the turning escape
